The paper introduces a game-theoretic model for resource allocation among selfish agents, which is a classic topic in algorithmic game theory (cs.GT). The problem involves solving a knapsack problem, which is a well-studied problem in computer science and optimization (cs.DS). The agents report valuations, which suggests the use of mechanism design and auction theory (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the communication complexity of the mechanism, which is related to information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper provides algorithmic results for computing Nash equilibria and analyzing the Price of Anarchy, which are relevant to algorithm design and analysis (cs.EC).
